<gap-fill>This is an offer for a job in Civil Engineering. It&apos;s about a job in Australia,
So if you&apos;re thinking about going there, listen to the job offer: 

Be part of a young, exciting and successful Civil Engineering team based in Canberra
 and get a salary of between <question-record><question></question><answer><text>$70,000 - $90,000</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> per year.
The job being offered is the position of a <question-record><question></question><answer><text>Civil Engineer for Urban Development</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>.

The Australian based, medium sized engineering consultancy has an urgent need for a Civil Engineer in the &amp;#x2018;Urban Developments&amp;#x2019; team based in Canberra. 

Originally <question-record><question></question><answer><text>established in Melbourne in 1953</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> this successful and expanding organization has <question-record><question></question><answer><text>4 offices across Australia with a 5th office based in Asia</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>. 

Their workload is mainly <question-record><question></question><answer><text>land development</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> with  4 main disciplines:
	1 - Urban Development and <question-record><question></question><answer><text>Civil Engineering</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>,
	2 - Major Roads,
	3 - Water &amp;#x0026; <question-record><question></question><answer><text>Environment</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>,
	4 - <question-record><question></question><answer><text>Building Structures</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>.

The Canberra office has both an Urban Development and a Roads&amp;#x0026;Traffic team working for both <question-record><question></question><answer><text>public and private</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> sector clients. With over <question-record><question></question><answer><text>200 members of staff across Australia and 38 of these based in Canberra</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>, they have a strong, established and successful reputation across New South Wales, Queensland &amp;#x0026; Victoria

As a Civil Engineer you will be working on a variety of projects, for example:
- Master plans for  <question-record><question></question><answer><text>communities</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> 
- Major <question-record><question></question><answer><text>infrastructure</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> works, or,
- Water and Wastewater projects.

The responsibilities of this position will involve:
- The <question-record><question></question><answer><text>design and investigation</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> of conceptual designs
- The preparation of <question-record><question></question><answer><text>reports and master plans</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> 
- The preparation of detailed designs and documentation as well as
- Reports and technical information
 
To be considered for this position you must have <question-record><question></question><answer><text>5-7 years experience</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> in a similar role with demonstrated knowledge of <question-record><question></question><answer><text>construction principles</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> and industry regulations. You must also be <question-record><question></question><answer><text>degree qualified with a Bachelor of Civil Engineering</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>. Excellent <question-record><question></question><answer><text>written and verbal communication</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record> are a must as well as a demonstrated ability to work on your own as well as part of a team.

If this position is of interest and you meet the above criteria, please contact Rebecca Frank at our company on <question-record><question></question><answer><text>00 61 293 21 55 00</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><answer><text>0061293215500</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct></answer><clue></clue></question-record>.</gap-fill>
